{
    "Description": "<h3>Usage</h3><pre class=\"ql-syntax\" spellcheck=\"false\">Node:isKey()\n</pre><ul><li><code><strong>Node</strong></code>: A column node within a table node tree to check for primary key status.</li></ul><p><br></p><h3><strong>Notes</strong></h3><ul><li>This function <strong>only works with table node trees</strong>.</li><li>Useful for identifying which field in a row acts as the unique identifier, especially when iterating over schema-defined tables like VMDs.</li><li>Helps ensure correct logic when merging or indexing data.</li></ul><p><br></p><h3><strong>Returns</strong></h3><ul><li><code>true</code> if the column is the primary key, <code>false</code> otherwise. <em><u>(bool)</u></em></li></ul><p><br></p><h3>Example</h3><pre class=\"ql-syntax\" spellcheck=\"false\">local T = db.tables{vmd = 'demo.vdb', name = 'Patient'}\nif T.Patient[1].Id:isKey() then\n&nbsp; &nbsp;trace(\"Id is the primary key for the Patient table.\")\nend\n</pre><ul><li>In this example, <code>isKey()</code> confirms whether the <code>Id</code> column of the <code>Patient</code> table is the designated primary key.</li><li>To allow this to work in translator, create a vdb file called <code>demo</code>. Then edit the file and create a table called <code>Patient</code>. Now edit the definition of the Patient table and add some columns including one named <code>Id</code>. <code>IsKey()</code> will return true or false depending on if that column is a key (whether the key checkbox is checked).</li></ul>",
    "Name": "node:isKey",
    "Parameters": null,
    "ParameterTable": false,
    "SummaryLine": "Determines if a column is the primary key for the table node."
}